What a weekend well spent at @jumeirahfrankfurt 💙 Amazing hotel with amazing staff and prime location right in the heart of town! I have never thought so much about visiting Frankfurt before, but I am glad I did visit this city! It is a very walkable city and residents and tourists alike use this bridge. If you want to walk from Frankfurt’s downtown to the neighborhood of Sachsenhausen, consider using this wonderful pedestrian bridge built in the year of 1868. Although the Eiserner Steg is one of several bridges that spans across the Main River, the river that intersects Frankfurt’s Sachsenhausen and downtown, it is the only walking bridge. It’s also the site for thousands of locks of love❤️ It is called Iron Bridge in English. What a fantastic view of the Frankfurt’s skyline!
#jumeirahfrankfurt
#staydifferent
#sassychris1germany
.
.

Have you ever been to Frankfurt? Well this is my first time💫From my Skyline Junior Suite @jumeirahfrankfurt I enjoyed 180 degree panoramic view of this Germany’s Financial Capital and I think I am in love already!
Sincere thanks to @jumeirahfrankfurt team who gave me a sweet surprise - what a warm welcome 🙏🏼☺️ yup, I came all the way from Jakarta to Frankfurt to discover what the city has to offer😉 So stay tuned and let’s find out in the next couple of days! In the mean time wishing you a good night from here ✨
#jumeirahfrankfurt
